<TEXT>
karlmarxstadt east germany ap karl marx looks awfully 
angry as he stares at a city that no longer practices his 
principles and no longer wants his name 
the imposing twostory bust of socialisms intellectual 
architect rests on a massive block of granite in front of city 
hall staring sternfaced across a main avenue that also sports his 
name 
the area around it is empty of people but nearby streets are 
crawling with commerce hundreds of booths stands and trucks 
loaded with western merchandise fill plazas and malls the 
frontline forces of capitalisms advancing army 
like virtually every other major population center in east 
germany karl marx the city has become karl marx the market one 
of the places to be if you have something to sell 
you can do a lot of business here it is incredible said 
jochen siebke head of marketing for the west german branch of 
citroen the french automaker 
this 825yearold city was known as chemnitz until 1953 when 
the former communist government changed the name in an april 
referendum 76 percent of those voting said the city of 308000 
should be changed back to chemnitz 
the city council has not yet formalized the change however and 
the drab industrial town is known alternately by both names 
highway signs switch back and forth and the government news 
agency adn uses a karlmarxstadtchemnitz dateline on 
stories from the city 
if the city is still somewhat schizophrenic about its name 
there is little doubt about which ideology is prevailing 
furniture is peddled from the backs of trucks and a seemingly 
endless string of booths sell everything from barbie dolls to black 
amp decker tools 
in a plaza models cavort to a michael jackson song and tout a 
line of surf wear the show takes place under a banner that says 
test the west west is a brand of cigarette 
citroen recently parked a dozen of its shiny cars on a dusty 
parking lot in town set up tables under redandwhite parasols and 
blared music and commercials touting its sleek sets of wheels 
the automaker wasnt necessarily looking to sell cars today 
siebke said but after july 2 when the german states merge their 
economies and east germans can convert their money to coveted west 
german marks 
you have to get out here get youre name known siebke 
said its in preparation for the whole economic union 
the cheapest car sells for about 9000 about 1800 more than 
the average east germans annual salary 
about half of the people who come by cannot pay and many work 
in outmoded industries that are likely to face high unemployment 
siebke says 
we dont press people to buy he said 
but he added that many people have large savings accounts 
people have been saving for 20 years but they have had 
nothing to buy he said one man came here and he had a savings 
account book with 500000 east marks in it 
under the conversion system that will be worth about 252000 
west german marks or 152000 after july 2 
prime minister lothar de maiziere has urged east germans to 
refrain from spending their new currency so they will not erode its 
value and cause inflation in both germanys 
but wolfgang hufenbecher director of the west german 
commerzbank and the head of its new east german operation said the 
influx of western products may be too tempting 
you can see that already he said speaking in east berlin 
recently lots of west german companies put out various goods at 
rather high prices but people still buy it there is a lot of 
money around 
he said average east german savings accounts range from the 
equivalents of 3010 to 6020 
last week trabant workers staged a brief strike in the nearby 
city of zwickau to demand protection from the unemployment expected 
as outmoded enterprises try to compete with their inferior products 
it is ironic of course siebke said east germans will 
accelerate the decline of their own industries by buying western 
products 
