china has detonated a nuclear device 
with at least twice the destructive force of the bomb dropped on 
hiroshima its first nuclear weapons test in nearly two years 
swedish monitors reported 
seismic signals indicated the explosion occurred at the lop nor 
test site in the far western province of xinjiang nilsolov 
bergqvist of the swedish defense research establishment at the 
hagfors observatory said wednesday 
the last chinese test was sept 29 1988 when beijing tested a 
low magnitude bomb of less than 10 kilotons bergqvist said by 
telephone 
the seismic indicators detected saturday registered 58 on the 
richter scale and indicated a bomb with a yield of 40 to 50 
kilotons according to the governmentrun observatory 
one kiloton has the explosive force of 1000 tons of tnt the 
bomb dropped on hiroshima japan during world war ii had an 
explosive force of 20 kilotons 
the chinese have conducted only four tests since 1984 
apparently restrained by the high cost of building and exploding a 
nuclear bomb 
china which set off its first atmospheric explosion in 1964 is 
the only nuclear nation that makes no announcements about its 
tests little is known about its nuclear capabilities 
it was only the second test this year of a nuclear weapon 
following an explosion at the us test site in nevada on march 10 
last year 27 tests were carried out around the world including 11 
by the united states and seven by the soviet union 
china insists that its nuclear weapons are solely for 
selfdefense and will never be used to strike first its nuclear 
arsenal is believed to include a halfdozen intercontinental 
ballistic missiles and more than 100 mediumrange ballistic 
missiles 
