for moyobamba wednesday afternoon carrying a team of 10 doctors and 
emergency supplies two more planes filled with rescue supplies 
were to leave today 
health department workers have been on a nationwide strike for 
two months but a union official in lima said wednesday that 
workers were helping with emergency plans 
patricia vargas llosa the wife of presidential candidate mario 
vargas llosa visited the area on wednesday accompanied by former 
president fernando belaunde terry 
the people there are terrorized because the ground is still 
shaking said mrs vargas llosa on her return to lima she said 
many people were being treated in tent hospitals for fractures and 
other injuries 
belaunde terry said the worst damage appeared to be in soritor 
and the nearby town of porvenir 
the temblor came two days before the 20th anniversary of a 
devastating earthquake that killed 70000 people in the northern 
andes mountains 
that quake the most deadly natural disaster ever recorded in 
the western hemisphere registered 77 on the richter scale an 
estimated 20000 people in the city of yungay were killed that day 
buried in mud and ice that came crashing down from a nearby 
mountain 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph a quake of a magnitude of 5 can cause considerable 
damage 
</TEXT>
