have brought life in this city of 8 million people to a standstill 
the army also was patrolling hyderabad a city of 3 million 
people 150 miles to the north after clashes there killed at least 
180 people 
the trouble is rooted in deep hatred between native sindhis and 
the mohajirs descendants of moslem indians who immigrated to 
pakistan during the 1947 partition of the subcontinent sindhis 
accuse the bettereducated mohajirs of taking the best jobs and 
most valuable land 
police blame the latest violence on a militant faction of the 
mohajir qami movement a small political party representing the 
moslem indian immigrants the party is demanding recognition as 
pakistans fifth nationality along with the pathans punjabis 
baluch and sindhis 
the prime minister had planned to leave june 3 on a fourday 
trip to qatar iraq kuwait and bahrain to drum up support for 
pakistan in its dispute with india over the kashmir region moslem 
secessionists there are trying to break away from hindudominated 
india india blames pakisan a moslem country for fomenting that 
unrest but pakistan denies the charge 
ms bhuttos aides said today the two weeks of random shootings 
and clashes between rival ethnic groups and security forces in 
pakistan had forced her to delay her trip aides said 
the prime minister has decided to delay her trip until some 
normalcy returns said one aide speaking on condition of 
anonymity 
