powerful nation that will be formed when east germany is merged 
with west germany but us officials said there would be no 
retreat from that position nor any deal cut by bush to scale down 
the size of the new german army 
gorbachevs reservations are behind a soviet slowdown in 
multilateral negotiations to cut conventional forces in europe 
including troop levels tanks aircraft helicopters and other 
nonnuclear weapons 
and the issue has clouded other key issues on the summit agenda 
including a framework agreement to slash longrange nuclear 
missiles a halt in the production of chemical weapons and a 
commercial pact to nearly quadruple travel between the two nations 
gorbachev has said time and again as he did in ottawa on 
wednesday that for a united germany to rejoin nato in an era of 
sweeping change and cooperation throughout europe would be a cold 
war affront to the sensibilities of the soviet people who suffered 
greater losses than any other to nazi germany in world war ii 
canadas prime minister brian mulroney expressed some sympathy 
for that point saying he hoped each side would explore 
alternatives 
american and soviet representatives for the fifth day held a 
round of talks at the state department to try to overcome the 
negotiating slump on conventional forces and to expand on the 
categories of longrange nuclear weapons to be reduced in another 
treaty 
