did not resume in the afternoon everybody would like to see 
things progress but there isnt a lot of progress a us 
official said they are waiting for the rest of the team 
the only evident accomplishment over the four days was an 
agreement tuesday on a definition of tanks and armored personnel 
carriers this will make it easier to reduce us and soviet 
arsenals of the weapons and also to police compliance with a treaty 
but the two leaders will issue joint statements setting goals 
and calling for quick followup talks on future nuclear and 
conventional cutbacks once a new strategic arms reduction treaty is 
finished us officials said 
baker who made arrangements to meet separately at the white 
house with soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze said 
last thursday that bush would press gorbachev at the summit to 
accelerate the troop reduction negotiations 
but gorbachev who got the ball rolling in the first place by 
volunteering to withdraw red army units and tanks from eastern and 
central europe threatened on friday to reconsider his policies if 
the western allies kept insisting on nato membership for germany 
the soviets suffered a loss of at least 20 million people in 
world war ii and with the warsaw pact weakening gorbachev is 
concerned about the reemergency of german military power 
administration officials said last thursday that bush will cut 
no deal with gorbachev to limit german troops but he is prepared 
to discuss a formula that might scale down the size of the red army 
as well 
