tainted by bovine spongiform encephalitis the nervous disorder 
known as mad cow disease 
taking up britains cause the european community on thursday 
criticized the french action and demanded the ban be lifted 
but french agriculture minister henri nallet said the ban will 
stay in place at least until the return this weekend of a team of 
french veterinarians sent to britain to assess the disease 
nallet acknowledged that his difficult decision had been 
denounced abroad but said he acted to avert worry and panic 
among french consumers 
