transmitted through cattle feeds they use sheep offal as a protein 
supplement 
the british government is sponsoring research on the disease 
which was identified in britain in 1986 the outbreak has largely 
been confined there 
the disease which has killed 13648 cows in britain eats holes 
in the brains of infected cattle and makes their tissue spongy 
