<TEXT>
lower prices and higher consumer incomes 
boosted the typical american familys ability to buy an existing 
singlefamily home in april a real estate trade group said thursday 
the national association of realtors said its housing 
affordability index reached 1046 in april up from 1039 in march 
that means a family earning the median income of 34032 had 
1046 percent of the income needed to qualify for conventional 
financing covering 80 percent of a medianpriced home costing 
95300 
the median income means half the families earned more and half 
less the median price means half of the homes cost more half less 
the median price of a home in april declined 1000 from march 
meaning the income needed to qualify for a loan dropped 96 to 
32544 at the same time the median family income rose 108 
realtors president norman d flynn said the typical price of an 
existing home in many cities is below the national median 
the commerce department reported on wednesday that the median 
price of a new home was 135900 in april but analysts generally 
agreed that reflected a big jump in new home sales in the expensive 
northeastern market that month the median had been 119400 in 
march 
the housing affordability index would have been higher in april 
the realtors said except for an increase in the interest rate used 
to compute the index from 1007 percent in march to 1015 percent in 
april 
the mortgage rate used to calculate the index is a composite of 
closing rates offered for both fixedrate mortgages and 
adjustablerate mortgages for existing homes as reported by the 
federal housing finance board 
we do expect a gradual decline in rates in the third quarter to 
stimulate a healthy home buying season this summer said john a 
tuccillo the realtors chief economist 
the realtors said the changes in the index home price mortgage 
rate and income resulted in a 2 decrease in monthly mortgage 
payments to 678 
under aprils affordability conditions the realtors said a 
family earning 20000 would qualify for a 58500 home using a 
46800 loan a family earning 30000 would qualify for a 87500 
home with a 70200 loan a family earning 40000 would qualify for 
a 117000 home with a 93600 loan and a family with 50000 
income would qualify for a 146300 home with a 117000 loan 
but flynn noted buyers may still face a major hurdle in obtaining 
down payments even with incomes sufficient to qualify for loans 
