<TEXT>
east german lawmakers thursday gave the 
government broad powers to seize land houses and businesses 
controlled by the privileged elite of the old communist regime 
the action freezes the partys vast holdings amassed after it 
came to power after world war ii just four weeks before the nation 
merges its economy with west germanys and begins shifting state 
property to the private sector 
lawmakers also voted to remove the old communist insignia a 
hammer and drafting compass from state buildings 
the government of prime minister lothar de maiziere had asked 
parliament to let him form a commission that would have the power to 
wrest away the holdings of the many organizations that existed under 
the former government 
de maiziere is to form the commission in the coming days after 
which all land buildings and enterprises owned by the communists 
would be held in trust pending an investigation of their value and 
legitimacy 
the new law also gives the commission power to interrogate 
witnesses search houses and seize evidence during its investigation 
the law calls for a system to be set up under which the 
government could reclaim the property in the public interest even 
if the property is in other countries 
the proposal came as the young democratic government grapples 
with the monumental task of converting stateowned property to 
private ownership a prerequisite to unification with west germany 
the german states are to merge their economies and social 
institutions on july 2 when west german currency will become the 
currency of east germany 
the independent property commission is to report its findings to 
parliament just two days before the economic union becomes official 
lawmaker gregor gysi leader of the reconstituted communist party 
that now supports a form of democratic socialism sharply criticized 
the proposal during a bitter ninehour parliament session 
they want all opposition eliminated said gysi whose party 
is now called the party of democratic socialism that is the goal 
and nothing else 
he said his party already has surrendered a large part of its 
property 
richard schroeder leader of the social democratic lawmakers in 
parliament said the proposal is aimed at shedding light on who owns 
what in the country 
we should bring clarity and light to the property proportion 
he said we have the impression that the history of the former 
communist party property is still being written 
the property investigation would cover all parties unions and 
organizations that came into being after 1945 but is clearly aimed 
at the assets of the old regime 
it would technically include de maizieres own christian 
democrats who were allowed to exist as a formal party 
large amounts of property are believed held by former communists 
prosecutors on thursday charged a former district communist party 
chief from the city of erfurt gerhard mueller with breach of trust 
and theft the government news agency adn said 
mueller 62 was arrested in december he is accused of building 
a luxurious hunting lodge with three baths at a cost of 210000 in 
public money 
many questions remain about the pace and process of distributing 
land and industries owned by the state to private hands 
west germany wants west germans to be able to reclaim any 
property they lost in east germany when the communists came to 
power east germany wants its citizens to have first crack at the 
property 
east germans are expected to face a rough transition to a free 
market in july widespread joblessness and rising prices are 
expected as socialist subsidies are eliminated and outmoded 
statesupported factories are forced to compete 
east germans fearing higher prices have been lining up at grocery 
stores to stock up on food and other household goods creating huge 
shortages of meat milk and other necessities officials said 
lawmaker vera wollenberger said meat was selling out in stores 
within one hour of opening in the cities of east berlin and halle 
commerce minister sybille reider said consumer demand has 
increased 300 percent to 400 percent in recent days soap bread and 
other goods are selling out she said 
