were badly hurt ambulance officials said 
the quake hit when bucharests streets were crowded with 
lunchhour shoppers and pedestrians it lasted about 45 seconds and 
was the third major earthquake since 1977 with its epicenter in the 
romanian carpathians 
the uppsala seismological center in sweden said it was felt so 
widely because it was about 63 miles deep 
i think it was this deafening sound of cracking walls that 
scared people said clerical worker sica burcea 52 the 
building was swinging horizontally and vertically we were lucky 
only to have some cracks in the walls i shivered when i realized 
1977 was coming back 
more than 1500 romanians died in a 1977 earthquake 
the richter scale gauges the amount of energy released by a quake 
as measured by the ground motion on seismographs a quake measuring 
6 can cause severe damage one of magnitude 7 is considered a major 
earthquake 
