an earthquake measuring 61 on the richter 
scale shook metropolitan mexico city early thursday sending 
frightened residents into the streets the red cross reported no 
injuries or major damage 
the 135 am jolt which lasted 15 seconds was centered about 
180 miles southwest of this quakeprone capital according to the 
us geological surveys national earthquake information center at 
golden colo 
hotel clerks in acapulco said the quake was felt in the pacific 
resort but that there was no damage 
mexico city spread across a basin prone to earthquakes suffered 
one of the centurys most devastating temblors on sept 19 1985 
that earthquake which measured 81 and an aftershock the next 
day left 9500 people dead and 150000 homeless 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs 
an earthquake measuring 6 can cause severe damage a 7 reading is 
a major earthquake capable of widespread heavy damage 8 is a 
great quake capable of tremendous damage 
