former philippines first lady imelda marcos 
collapsed and coughed up blood thursday during her federal 
racketeering trial and was taken by ambulance to a hospital 
mrs marcos who twice in the last month had fallen ill with high 
blood pressure was carried out on a stretcher an oxygen mask on 
her face and was taken to new york hospital 
tests showed evidence of bleeding in her stomach said jonathan 
weil a hospital spokesman her condition was listed as stable 
he said doctors concluded that she has erosive gastritis a 
condition in which acid produced by the stomach erodes the organs 
lining 
mrs marcos 60 was treated with intravenous medication to 
suppress the production of acid weil said 
it is expected that she will be in the hospital for several 
days until her condition which is not lifethreatening has 
improved he said 
the spokesman said mrs marcos was alert conscious awake and 
not excessively in pain 
