june 10 deadline 
the latest agreement is one of a number reached between the 
contras and the government of president violetta barrios de chamorro 
the demobilization process was stopped by the contras once after 
a series of crippling strikes by the public sector in which the 
sandinistaled strikers got virtually everything they wanted 
the contras said this made them worry about the stability of the 
government in the face of the sandinista opposition 
the contras with american backing fought the leftist sandinista 
regime for nine of the 10 years it held power in a war that cost 
about 30000 lives 
the sandinista newspaper barricada said thursday that the 
government gave the contras too much 
it said the deal lacks an obligatory clause that offers the 
citizenry guarantees on the disarmament of the contras 
mrs chamorro said wednesday that gen humberto ortega the 
former sandinista defense minister who remains in charge of the 
army will develop a plan to reduce the armys size after the 
contras have disarmed 
her retention of ortega brother of former sandinista president 
daniel ortega also has been a point of controversy among the 
contras and one of a number of pressures on her new administration 
