<TEXT>
in swedish sports history harry 
persson was a tragic figure 
a talented heavyweight he went to the united states in 1926 to 
try to take the world boxing title from jack dempsey he was beaten 
by his own naivete and honesty 
now two swedes are putting perssons story to music for a 
fulllength opera commissioned by the royal opera house 
it is a tearjerker full of hard punches against the tear 
glands said novelist torbjorn savfe author of the libretto the 
score is being composed by larsake frankeblom for a 1992 
premiere 
savfe said the opera understood to be the first written about a 
boxer is full of ring action even the statue of liberty wears a 
boxing glove in one scene 
the music is modern interwoven with hits from the 1920s 
persson was a stone worker with a rockhard right who beat every 
european he met in the ring he was an idol whose popularity in the 
economically depressed sweden of the 20s matched that of another 
sports hero of the early 80s tennis champion bjorn borg 
the americans longed for a european who could match jack 
dempsey savfe said dempsey was heavyweight champion 19191926 
persson crossed the atlantic with hopes of punching his way to 
wealth and fame his swedish compatriot the late actress greta 
garbo arrived a year ahead of him 
but reality dealt persson a knockout blow he was confronted by 
a boxing world controlled by cheats and intriguers anyone who 
refused to play by their rules was crushed 
persson was the honest swede filled with romantic ideas of the 
american dream of success he believed he could beat his way to the 
gold through good craftsmanship savfe said he was completely 
outwitted 
persson began well defeating johnny risco carl carter and jack 
adams 
but persson insisted on doing things his way he refused to fire 
his swedish manager and sign on with american promoters suddenly 
he started losing 
in a match against bud gorman persson was disqualified for 
hitting below the belt after gorman had lifted his shorts high over 
his abdomen 
he lost on points against pat mccarthy although he won 10 
rounds he was the victim of con tricks safve said 
persson never got a chance to meet dempsey he returned to 
sweden in 1927 disillusioned his boxing career virtually over 
his wife took his money and their son and deserted him savfe said 
the staging of the opera includes several of perssons 
successful matches and his disqualification in the gorman fight in 
a final scene four years after he returns to sweden a fallen hero 
persson fights norwegian otto von porat 
he goes down and just sits on the mat in the ring after the 
first blow in the first round and he shakes his head the tragedy 
is completed savfe said 
persson died in 1979 at age 81 savfe said no one visited him 
in a sanatorium outside stockholm during the last seven years of 
his life 
sweden got a world heavyweight champion in 1959 when ingemar 
johansson beat floyd patterson patterson retook the title a year 
later johansson is now 57 and occasionally appears as a sports 
commentator on television 
