<TEXT>
early research at the argonne national 
laboratory helped create nuclear power but now scientists there 
are turning crop waste into plastic unlocking the secrets of 
photosynthesis and preparing to study soil with a powerful new 
xray 
the laboratorys basic mission of energy research has produced 
spinoffs that could help farmers produce food and find new markets 
advances in agriculture are most likely to occur as a result 
of the application of modern science and thats precisely what 
were attempting to do lab director alan schriesheim said 
argonne which opened in 1946 with a mission of finding peaceful 
uses for atomic energy has 1700 acres 25 miles southwest of 
chicago rare white deer roam the grounds 
part of the us department of energy it is operated under 
