considering both paris and london as possible sites for the 12 
billion project trying to determine which location offers better 
financial opportunities 
rocard according to his office told the visitors he was 
amenable to the proposal provided that mca addressed environmental 
concerns and cooperated fully with the french tv and film industry 
mcas final decision is expected within the next few months and 
the complex is tentatively scheduled to be opened in 1993 
the proposed site in france is melunsenart a new suburb being 
developed about 20 miles southeast of paris 
the complex would include a golf course hotels with 5000 rooms 
a hightech industrial park oriented toward the audiovisual 
industry production studios and an amusement park 
mca which is based in universal city calif has projected 5 
million visitors to the park in its first year and estimates the 
complex would create 12000 jobs 
about 20 miles north of the site foundations are being laid for 
euro disneyland an even bigger project scheduled for opening in 
1992 disney executives anticipate 11 million visitors in the first 
year and have estimated the total cost of the undertaking at 76 
billion 
british officials have been trying to woo mca with a 1600acre 
site on the outskirts of london their hopes are based in part on 
the premise that the company might shy away from direct competition 
with euro disneyland 
there is evidence however that mca wont back away it has 
