grain and soybean futures closed mostly higher 
thursday on the chicago board of trade as weather concerns continued 
to dominate trading activity 
corn futures were pushed lower selling by professional traders 
and funds and a national weather service sixto10day forecast 
that called for more favorable planting weather 
