and a dry spell could allow farmers to catch up said william 
biedermann an analyst with allendale inc in chicago 
soybean futures were higher on conjecture that the amount of corn 
acreage given over to soybeans may not be as large as expected 
biedermann said because soybeans mature more quickly than corn 
farmers usually plant soybeans when corn planting is delayed into 
june 
